The paper introduces a new algorithm for hierarchical clustering and extends existing algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), databases (cs.DB), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on clustering algorithms and their performance, the first three sub-categories are the most likely.
